      "comment": "HAMMOON HEROINE (5) is racing well, scoring by 1.75 lengths two back at Kembla Grange then finishing a respectable fourth last time over 1600m at Canberra when not too far away. Has the pace to be in a prominent position from the outset. Will play a major role. OBSIDIAN DREAM (6) got off the mark over 1400m at this track last start, scoring by 0.8 lengths. Sparingly raced and has more to offer. Reunites with Sam Clipperton who was on board last start. Sure to prove tough to beat again with that win now under her belt. ROSE WATER (7) is yet to find the winners' list this time in work but has three placings from four starts this campaign, finishing 2.75 lengths away in third most recently over 1412m at Taree. Sure to be competitive. CLEAR BLUE DAY (3) is a progressive colt who closed off well in a fairly decent race when third over 1600m at this course on a Heavy (8) surface. Can race a touch closer and has solid each-way prospects.",
